Dear Jamie,
I cant even remember the day that me and you first laid eyes on each other .. but I know that as soon as it happened it was a friendship made in heaven. From exchanging gifts EVERY christmas to you not wanting to leave your parents in 1st grade... all the times you would get mad at me and lock me out of your room.. falling in boxes...taking down your swing set, playing Barbies,power rangers, swimming in your pool. I remember i would come over and rusty would jump on me. Me and you always dress up and I even put on ur moms wedding dress! she was so pissed lol every time i look back on the past there is always a memory with you. I dont remember not knowing you! COuld u just imagine if one of us would have moved into a diff area? WE never would have met and my entire life would be completely different. STILL together  to this day! If u were not on this earth.. My soul would b ripped out and my heart would go along with it. You cross my mind 24/7 and your family is my family.. u were ther for me when my parents got divorced .. and when my family members passed away.. and u were the reason I needed stitches in my lip for running into the corner of the wall. but i wasnt even mad at you I still loved you and I always will i dont know how else to say it jme u make me who i am.. the Christine Marie Cichowski! We shaped each others lifes growing up.. and we are gonna grow older .. and get married and have kids .. and we will STILL b talking...STILL b crying... and laffing and singing! God puts you on earth to complete a journey and once you fulfill your journey god takes u to heaven. There is no way i can fulfill my journey without my Jamie Lynn! People say oh so and so is my best friend but i dont think anyone even knos what a best friend is. When I say "Jamie you're my best friend" its so truthful and its life longgg. I love you. I thank god for bringing you to me. (( Christine and Jamie Best Friends Forever))

Love christine
